# AI Assistant Behavior Guidelines

## Code Generation Standards
- Always generate TypeScript code with proper type annotations
- Use modern React patterns (functional components, hooks)
- Follow the project's established coding conventions
- Generate code that follows the project's architecture patterns
- Include proper error handling and validation

## Code Quality Requirements
- Generate clean, readable, and maintainable code
- Use meaningful variable and function names
- Include proper comments for complex logic
- Follow DRY (Don't Repeat Yourself) principles
- Generate code that passes linting and type checking

## Security Considerations
- Never generate code that exposes sensitive information
- Always validate user input in generated code
- Use proper authentication and authorization patterns
- Generate secure database queries and API endpoints
- Follow security best practices in all generated code

## Performance Optimization
- Generate optimized code that follows performance best practices
- Use proper React optimization patterns (memo, useMemo, useCallback)
- Generate efficient database queries and API calls
- Implement proper caching strategies where appropriate
- Consider bundle size and loading performance

## Testing Requirements
- Generate code that is testable and includes proper test cases
- Use proper mocking strategies for external dependencies
- Generate both unit and integration tests where appropriate
- Follow the project's testing patterns and conventions
- Include proper error case testing

## Documentation Standards
- Generate proper JSDoc comments for functions and components
- Include usage examples in generated code
- Document complex business logic and algorithms
- Generate proper README updates when adding new features
- Include proper API documentation for new endpoints

## Error Handling
- Always include proper error handling in generated code
- Use consistent error handling patterns across the project
- Generate proper error messages and logging
- Include proper fallback mechanisms for failed operations
- Follow the project's error handling conventions

## Accessibility
- Generate accessible code that follows WCAG guidelines
- Include proper ARIA attributes and semantic HTML
- Ensure keyboard navigation works correctly
- Generate proper focus management for dynamic content
- Include proper color contrast and visual accessibility

## Code Review Standards
- Generate code that is ready for code review
- Include proper commit messages and change descriptions
- Generate code that follows the project's review guidelines
- Include proper documentation for complex changes
- Generate code that is easy to understand and maintain

## Project-Specific Guidelines
- Follow the Adrata project's specific patterns and conventions
- Use the project's established libraries and frameworks
- Generate code that integrates well with existing systems
- Follow the project's data models and API patterns
- Use the project's established authentication and security patterns